Features:
	Two players no ai, players take turns
		- bonus feature ai support
	Restart after game end
	Player names (names will just act as login for possible persistence)
	Player score tracked from one game to another (non-persistent, only for game session)
		- bonus feature persistent state
	Help / tutorial
	Main Menu

Tic Tac Toe state:
	Player state:
		Human players:
			name
			score
	Board state:
		3x3 grid of cells with either x or o
	Game state:
		whose turn is it?
		what state is the game in?
			- main menu
			- playing
				- getting initial input
			- leaderboard
			- viewing help
		the board
	Application state
		Game state
		Render layer
		Input layer

Functionality:
	- Get input
	- Print text to the screen
	- Renderer that knows about the game state
	
	
	
Arcitecture






Screens:
---------------------------
Main Menu:
1. Play
2. Leaderboard
3. Help
4. Options
4. Exit

abstract class Screen
{
	Run()
}

PlayGame : Screen
{
	override Run()
}

Leaderboard : Screen
{
	override Run()
}

Help : Screen
{
	override Run()
	Exit()
}

States
	Play Game
	Leaderboards
	Help

Application

	// current session of multiple games
	Session session;
	
	// users selection determines which state class to use
	Menu menu;
	
	// currently selected state
	Screen screen;
	
	// executes state logic (essentially call state.Run() in a loop)
	GameLoop()
	

Main()
{
	Application app;
	app.Run();
	
	Application.Instance.Run();
}

----------------------------------
**DIAMOND OF DEATH**

		A
	   / \
      B   C
       \ /
        D	   


class A
{
	void Foo();
}

class B : A
{
	override void Foo();
};

class C : A
{
	override void Foo();
};

class D : B, C
{
	override void Foo()
	{
	    base.Foo();
	}
};



